Class PgxToken

  • java.lang.Object
    • PgxToken

  • public class PgxToken
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides helper methods for using the new authentication mechanism introduced in Oracle Graph 20.3

        public static oracle.pgx.api.ServerInstance getInstance(java.lang.String baseUrl,
                                                        java.lang.String username,
                                                        java.lang.String password)
                                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Returns a ServerInstance object authenticated using the provided user name and password. It first obtains an authentication token from the PGX server, then establishes a connection with the PGX server using that token, and returns a ServerInstance object.
        Parameters:
        baseUrl - The URL of the PGX server providing the authentication
        username - The username to authenticate
        password - The password of that username

      • getHeader

        public java.lang.String getHeader()
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Returns the header of the authentication token. The authentication token is formed of three base64-encoded strings. The first one contains the token "header". This method decodes the header and returns the decoded JSON string.
        Returns:
        a String with the token header.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • getPayload

        public java.lang.String getPayload()
                            throws java.lang.Exception
        Returns the payload of the authentication token. The authentication token is formed of three base64-encoded strings. The second one contains the token "payload". This method decodes the payload and returns the decoded JSON string.
        Returns:
        a String with the token payload.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • getSignature

        public java.lang.String getSignature()
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Returns the signature of the authentication token. The authentication token is formed of three base64-encoded strings. The third one contains the token "signature". This method returns the signature in base64 encoding.
        Returns:
        a String with the token signature.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • dump

        public void dump()
          throws java.lang.Exception
        Prints full details about the token. Shows the full JSON token response received from the PGX server, as well as the decoded header, payload and signature, when it was issued, and when it expires.

        java.lang.Exception
